<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Engagement Letter — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Engagement Letter</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Active Recovery Engagement</div>
    <h1>Engagement<br/>Letter</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      This letter sets out the terms under which
      {{ investigator.organization }} will pursue active recovery of
      the stolen funds identified in our initial diagnostic. Please
      review carefully and sign at Section 8 to engage.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Between</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.organization }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.name }}, Investigator of record<br/>{{ investigator.email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>And</dt>
      <dd>{{ victim.name }}<span class="secondary">{% if victim.email %}{{ victim.email }}<br/>{% endif %}{% if victim.address %}{{ victim.address }}{% endif %}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Reference</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Affected Wallet</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<h2>1. Background</h2>
<p>
  On {{ diagnostic_completed_at }}, Recupero completed a forensic
  trace of the wallet at <span class="mono">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</span>
  on {{ chain_display }} pursuant to your $499 initial-assessment
  engagement. The trace identified
  <strong>{{ total_freezable_usd }}</strong>
  in confirmed-recoverable stolen funds held under
  {{ freezable_issuer_count }} {{ "issuer's" if freezable_issuer_count == 1 else "issuers'" }}
  protocol-level authority, plus an additional
  <strong>{{ total_under_investigation_usd }}</strong>
  in positions pending issuer KYC verification. The findings are
  documented in the diagnostic report previously delivered to you.
</p>
<p>
  You have indicated you wish to engage Recupero for active recovery
  of these funds. This letter sets out the terms of that engagement.
</p>

<h2>2. Scope of services</h2>
<p>
  Under this engagement, {{ investigator.organization }} will:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    Within <strong>5 business days</strong> of your signature, send
    the prepared compliance freeze-request letter to each of the
    {{ freezable_issuer_count }} identified
    {{ "issuer's" if freezable_issuer_count == 1 else "issuers'" }}
    compliance teams. Copies of every letter sent will be provided
    to you.
  </li>
  <li>
    Within <strong>5 business days</strong> of your signature, send
    the law-enforcement handoff package to the recommended filing
    channels (see Section 6.1 of the LE handoff). You retain
    independent rights to file with additional channels.
  </li>
  <li>
    Follow up with each issuer's compliance desk on a documented
    cadence (typically every 5-7 business days) until they confirm
    acknowledgement and provide a substantive response.
  </li>
  <li>
    Coordinate with the law-enforcement officer assigned to your
    case (if filed) — providing chain-of-evidence support, answering
    technical questions, and helping translate compliance-team
    responses into LE-actionable form.
  </li>
  <li>
    Provide weekly status reports to you in writing for
    <strong>30 days</strong> from the engagement date, with longer
    intervals thereafter if the case is still active.
  </li>
  <li>
    Promote INVESTIGATE-flagged positions to FREEZABLE as issuer
    KYC responses come in, and request hold extensions to cover
    them where appropriate.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>3. What this engagement does NOT include</h2>
<p>
  To set honest expectations, {{ investigator.organization }} does
  not promise or guarantee:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>That funds will actually be frozen or returned.</strong>
    Issuer cooperation is voluntary outside formal legal process.
    Even with a credible compliance request, an issuer may decline
    to act until law enforcement engages with formal subpoena or
    seizure order.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>A specific recovery timeline.</strong> Typical issuer
    response cycles are 1-4 weeks for substantive freeze decisions.
    Actual fund return, when it happens, typically occurs
    weeks-to-months after the freeze is placed.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Recovery of any specific amount.</strong> Partial
    recovery is the typical outcome. Funds marked INVESTIGATE may
    turn out to belong to KYC'd third parties unrelated to the
    perpetrator, in which case those positions are not recoverable.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Legal representation.</strong> Recupero is not a law
    firm. Nothing in this engagement constitutes legal advice or
    the practice of law. You retain the right to engage counsel
    independently; if a recovery action progresses to litigation
    or formal legal process, you will need to retain an attorney
    for that step.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Fees</h2>

<h3>Engagement fee</h3>
<p>
  The total engagement fee is <strong>{{ total_engagement_fee_text }}</strong>.
  Your $499 initial-assessment fee is credited against this total,
  so the incremental amount due upon signing is
  <strong>{{ incremental_engagement_fee_text }}</strong>.
</p>
<p>
  The incremental engagement fee is invoiced upon your signature and
  is due within 7 days of invoice. It is <strong>non-refundable</strong>
  once we have begun sending letters on your behalf — see Section 5
  for the limited refund condition before letter-sending commences.
</p>

<h3>Contingency fee</h3>
<p>
  In addition to the engagement fee, Recupero is entitled to
  <strong>{{ contingency_pct }}%</strong> of any funds actually
  recovered through the engagement. "Recovered" means funds returned
  to you or to a court-appointed custodian on your behalf, in
  USD-equivalent value at the time of return.
</p>
<p>
  The contingency fee is invoiced within 14 days of a recovery
  event and is due within 30 days of invoice. Recoveries that occur
  more than 12 months after the engagement date are not subject to
  the contingency fee unless they result from actions Recupero was
  actively pursuing at the time.
</p>

<h2>5. Termination</h2>
<p>
  Either party may terminate this engagement at any time by written
  notice (email to <a href="mailto:{{ investigator.email }}">{{ investigator.email }}</a>
  is sufficient).
</p>
<p>
  <strong>If you terminate</strong> before Recupero has sent the
  compliance freeze letters: a 75% refund of the incremental
  engagement fee is issued ($499 initial-assessment fee remains
  earned). After letters have been sent, the engagement fee is
  fully earned and non-refundable, but the contingency fee
  obligation terminates with respect to any recovery occurring more
  than 30 days after termination.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>If Recupero terminates</strong> before the compliance
  letters are sent: a full refund of the incremental engagement
  fee is issued.
</p>

<h2>6. Authority &amp; consent</h2>
<p>
  By signing this letter you authorize {{ investigator.organization }}
  to:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    Communicate with stablecoin issuers, exchanges, and law-enforcement
    agencies regarding this matter on your behalf, identifying you
    as the victim and citing your factual narrative as documented
    in the case file.
  </li>
  <li>
    Reference your case in aggregate statistics (e.g., "we have
    pursued recovery of $X in N cases") provided no
    individually-identifying information is disclosed.
  </li>
  <li>
    Retain the diagnostic artifacts (trace report, flow diagram,
    freeze letters, LE handoff) for the period required by
    record-keeping best practices and applicable law, typically
    7 years.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Confidentiality</h2>
<p>
  Recupero will not disclose personally identifying information
  about you to any party except (a) compliance teams and law
  enforcement engaged for the purpose of this recovery, (b) as
  required by valid legal process, or (c) as you authorize in
  writing. All communications regarding this matter are treated as
  confidential.
</p>

<h2>8. Governing law &amp; dispute resolution</h2>
<p>
  This engagement is governed by the laws of
  {% if investigator_jurisdiction %}{{ investigator_jurisdiction }}{% else %}the State of Delaware{% endif %}.
  Any dispute arising under this engagement that cannot be
  resolved by good-faith discussion will be submitted to
  binding arbitration administered by JAMS in
  {% if investigator_jurisdiction %}{{ investigator_jurisdiction }}{% else %}Delaware{% endif %},
  under JAMS' Streamlined Arbitration Rules.
</p>

<h2>9. Signature</h2>

<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    <strong>By signing below, you confirm that you have read this
    engagement letter in full, understand its terms (including the
    fee structure and the explicit limits on what Recupero promises),
    and authorize Recupero to begin the work described in Section 2.</strong>
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    Sign and return to <a href="mailto:{{ investigator.email }}">{{ investigator.email }}</a>
    — electronic signature acceptable.
  </p>
</div>

<table class="evidence" style="margin-top:2em;">
  <tr>
    <th style="width:50%;">For {{ victim.name }} (Client)</th>
    <th style="width:50%;">For {{ investigator.organization }}</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-fields">
        <strong>{{ victim.name }}</strong>
        Signature<br/>
        Date: __________________________
      </div>
    </td>
    <td>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-fields">
        <strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong>
        Investigator of record · {{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
        Date: __________________________
      </div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p class="small" style="margin-top:2em;">
  Recupero is not a law firm and does not provide legal advice.
  Nothing in this engagement letter constitutes the formation of
  an attorney-client relationship. For matters requiring legal
  representation, please consult an attorney licensed in your
  jurisdiction.
</p>


<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>Engagement {{ case_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Confidential.</span> Intended for {{ victim.name }}.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
